The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Airport township
                                                                                                               Airport township
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, July 16: The promoter of the Rs 10,000-crore airport township in Burdwans Andal today said it expected to receive the first plots of land in two to three months.        
	The announcement by Bengal Aerotropolis Project Limited (BAPL) came on a day Singapores Changi Airport International (CAI) said it would invest $20 million (Rs 97.4 crore) in BAPL by picking up 26 per cent stake.        
	The project has faced resistance from a Trinamul Congress-led save farmland committee that demanded Rs 18 lakh an acre against the government offer of Rs 7.5-11.5 lakh. Committee leaders today said they were yet to decide the next course of action but wanted the aerotropolis set up in Andal.        
	BAPL director and CEO Subrata Paul told a news conference: We expect to complete the acquisition process by the end of this year.                                                                                                                                                                            
